Subject: [PATCH 5/6] Detect SUID-sandbox failures on AppImage launches and warn before falling back to --no-sandbox

Recent Ubuntu / Debian derivatives (22.04+, and all kernels with
`kernel.unprivileged_userns_clone=0`) refuse to start Chromium's SUID
sandbox inside an AppImage. Upstream's user-visible failure is a cryptic
"Failed to move to new namespace" error with no mitigation hint.

The pragmatic fix is to relaunch with `--no-sandbox`, which upstream
allows via environment but does not document. We want to:

  1. Catch the sandbox failure (detectable via the GPU process exit
     code / the specific stderr pattern) on app startup.
  2. Log a clear warning to the user that the sandbox is disabled,
     with a link to the Live2D / Maker Lab docs page explaining why
     and how to re-enable it (enable unprivileged user namespaces).
  3. Relaunch with `--no-sandbox` appended.

This patch adds that flow in `src/main/index.ts`, gated on Linux +
AppImage (detected via `process.env.APPIMAGE`).

Applies against: vendor/open-llm-vtuber-web @ d176e7df2366952e3bacbf12cf9a8b18a4315932

